head_commit.message:
parser: ignore empty environment variables

Treat empty environment variables as "not set" to prevent template
placeholders (e.g., AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID="") from overwriting defaults.

This approach is debatable. If the community prefers empty strings to
override defaults, we can revert this and comment out empty variables in
kustomization templates instead.

This might be the root cause of pods failing with timeout because empty
env vars cause cloud provider initialization to fail silently,
preventing readiness probes from succeeding.

Signed-off-by: Beraldo Leal <bleal@redhat.com>

the peer pods v0.17.0 release get a fixed and compatible version of
the kata runtime deployed.
